3. `itemSlotPrefab`: the prefab for the inventory slots.

You can then use the `AddItem` function to add items to the inventory, and the `RemoveItem` function to remove items from the inventory.

The `InventoryItem` class represents an item in the inventory. It has an `id` (which can be used to identify the item), a `name`, a `stackable` flag (which is `true` for stackable items like potions), a `count` (which represents the number of items in the stack), and a `maxCount` (which is the maximum number of items in a stack).

The `InventorySlot` class represents a single slot in the inventory UI. It has a `SetItem` function, which takes an `InventoryItem` and updates the UI to show the item, and a `Clear` function, which clears the UI to show that there is no item in the slot.

